Visualize Results

Source: vignettes/visualize.Rmd
visualize.Rmd

Load example signature and genesets

Here we define our signature of interest as a group of genes randomly sampled from the estrogen-dependent gene expression geneset and use a genesets example from REACTOME.

signatures <- readRDS(system.file("extdata/signatures.rds", package="hypeR"))
signature <- signatures$signature

gsets <- readRDS(system.file("extdata/gsets.rds", package="hypeR"))
gsets <- gsets$REACTOME

Hyper enrichment

All workflows begin with performing hyper enrichment with hypeR.

hyp_obj <- hypeR(signature, gsets, bg=7842, fdr=0.05)

Plot results

One can visualize the top enriched pathways using hyp_plot which returns a horizontal bar plot. Each bar is a geneset, where dark blue represents the proportion of signature genes found in the entire geneset.

hyp_plot(hyp_obj, return_plots=TRUE)

Enrichment map

One can visualize the top enriched pathways using hyp_emap which will return an enrichment map. Each node represents a geneset, where the shade of red indicates the normalized significance of enrichment. Hover over the node to view the raw value. Edges represent geneset similarity, calculated by either jaccard or overlap similarity metrics.

hyp_emap(hyp_obj, similarity_cutoff=0.5, return_plots=TRUE)
